USE CASE DRAFT: T1078 Valid Accounts



ATTACK DESCRIPTION
Adversaries may obtain and abuse legitimate user credentials to access systems, applications, and network resources. More difficult to detect than brute force attacks, sicne activity appears to originate from authorized users.

ATT&CK Mapping
Technique ID: T1078
Technique name: Valid Accounts

Tactics:
- Initial Access(TA0001) - adversary trying to get into your network
- Privelege Escalation(TA0004) - adversary trying to gain higher level permissions
- Command and Control(TA0011) - adversary trying to communicate with compromised systems to control them

Detection Objective
Identify successful logins happening after multiple failed authentication attempts, which may indicate a hacker succesfully guessed or obtaiend valid credentials

Potential Data Sources
EventID 4648 - Logon using Explicit Credentials
EventID 4672 - Special Priveleges Assigned
EventID 4625 - Failed Logon
EventID 4624 - Succesful Logon

Detection Idea
Identify accounts that experience multiple failed logons followed by a succesful authentification

Examples of suspicious behavior:
- Multiple failures followed by a success
- Successful Login from New System
- Administrative Login After Repeated Failures


Investigation commands:
Successful Logins --> Failed and Successful Logins Together --> Most Active Accounts --> Priveleged Logins

Alert Concept

Succeccful Authentication Following Failed Logins
Trigger Condition: 1 or more EventID 4624 or 4625 events, followed by Event ID 4624, same account, Within a defined time window
Severity: Medium  --> High if Administrator account involved, domain admin involved, login originates from unusual host, priveleged activity follows authentication(any of these occur)

